Theory:

  Steps to install & configure:
    Before begin
1.	Create a Google Cloud Platform project, if you don't have one already.	
2.	Make sure that Python 2.7 is installed on your system: python -V
3.	Note: As of Cloud SDK version 206.0.0, the gcloud CLI has experimental support for running using a Python 3.4+ interpreter (run gcloud topic startup for exclusions and more information on configuring your Python interpreter). All other Cloud SDK tools still required Python 2.7 interpreter.
4.	The archive file best suited to your operating system. Most machines will run the 64-bit package. If you'd like to check, run uname -m to verify if you're running a 64-bit system.
