1. What is Google App Engine?

Answer:
Google App Engine is a Platform as a Service (PaaS) provided by Google Cloud that allows developers to deploy applications without managing servers. It automatically handles scaling, load balancing, and infrastructure management.

🔹 2. What is Google Cloud SDK?

Answer:
Google Cloud SDK is a set of command-line tools used to interact with Google Cloud services like App Engine, Compute Engine, and Storage. It includes the gcloud command.

🔹 3. What is the use of gcloud command?

Answer:
The gcloud command is used to:

Authenticate users
Create and manage projects
Deploy applications
Configure cloud resources
🔹 4. What is App Engine used for?

Answer:
App Engine is used to:

Deploy web applications
Automatically scale applications
Manage infrastructure without server configuration
🔹 5. What is the command to initialize SDK?

Answer:

gcloud init

It initializes SDK, logs in user, and sets default project.

🔹 6. What is the command to create App Engine application?

Answer:

gcloud app create

It creates an App Engine application in the selected project and region.

🔹 7. Why is region selected during App Engine creation?

Answer:
Region is selected to define:

Where the application will be hosted
Reduce latency
Improve performance based on user location

Example: asia-south1 for India

🔹 8. What is deployment?

Answer:
Deployment is the process of uploading application code to the cloud so it becomes publicly accessible.

🔹 9. Command to deploy application?

Answer:

gcloud app deploy
🔹 10. Command to open deployed app?

Answer:

gcloud app browse

It opens the deployed web application in browser.

🔹 11. What is PaaS?

Answer:
Platform as a Service provides a cloud platform where developers can deploy applications without managing hardware or operating systems.

🔹 12. What is the advantage of App Engine?

Answer:

No server management
Auto scaling
Pay-as-you-use model
Easy deployment
High availability
🔹 13. What is a project in Google Cloud?

Answer:
A project is a container that holds all Google Cloud resources like App Engine apps, storage, and APIs.

🔹 14. Why is billing required in App Engine?

Answer:
Billing is required because:

Google needs payment verification
Some resources are chargeable
Ensures controlled usage of cloud services
🔹 15. What happens if billing is not enabled?

Answer:
App Engine cannot be created or deployed, and the command will show:

“Permission denied or billing account required”

🔹 16. What is Hello World application?

Answer:
It is a simple sample application used to test deployment. It displays "Hello World" to confirm successful setup.

🔹 17. What is the use of app.yaml?

Answer:
It is a configuration file that tells App Engine:

Runtime environment
Service type
Application settings
🔹 18. What is gcloud auth list used for?

Answer:
It shows all logged-in Google accounts and indicates the active account.

🔹 19. What is gcloud config list?

Answer:
It displays:

Active account
Project ID
Configuration settings
🔹 20. Difference between local run and cloud deployment?

Answer:

Local Run	Cloud Deployment
Runs on your system	Runs on Google servers
Not public	Public URL
Temporary	Permanent hosting
🔥 IMPORTANT HIGH-LEVEL QUESTIONS (FOR EXTRA MARKS)
🔹 21. Why do we use App Engine instead of traditional servers?

Answer:
Because App Engine removes the need for:

Server maintenance
Manual scaling
Infrastructure management
🔹 22. What is auto scaling?

Answer:
Auto scaling means the system automatically increases or decreases resources based on traffic.

🔹 23. Is App Engine free?

Answer:
It has a free tier, but usage beyond limits requires billing.

🔹 24. What is the output of successful deployment?

Answer:
A live URL like:

https://project-id.appspot.com

which shows the application in browser.

🔹 25. What error did you face during setup?

Answer (your real case):
Billing account was not attached, so App Engine creation was restricted.